The paper discusses a machine learning problem related to regression and feature selection. Specifically, it focuses on ordinal regression and the identification of feature relevance bounds. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), statistics (cs.ST), and cryptography and security (cs.CR). However, given the focus on machine learning and regression, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CV due to the potential application of ordinal regression in computer vision tasks. The other two sub-categories are less likely but still possible, as they also involve statistical and predictive modeling.
